parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, slip, or stall, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle jerks or surges forward
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle stalls
or the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the ignition switch is difficult to turn
the ignition switch fails to turn
the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective replacement of the ignition switch can cause the new switch to fail prematurely, leading to additional repair costs and safety risks.
symptoms: The new ignition switch fails to function properly
the new ignition switch fails prematurely
the vehicle stalls without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of recall repairs can leave vehicles on the road with known safety issues, increasing the risk of accidents or other safety problems.
symptoms: Parts are not available for recall repairs
dealerships do not know when parts will be available
recall repairs are delayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Additional Problems Caused by Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall repairs can cause additional problems, such as damage to other components or systems, leading to additional repair costs and safety risks.
symptoms: Other components or systems fail after recall repairs
additional problems arise after recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ball joint failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, damage to the vehicle, and potential injury to occupants.
symptoms: Vehicle spins out of control
sways from side to side
loud noises or clunking sounds from the front suspension
especially in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise from the front suspension can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Loud and distinct cracking or clunking noise from the front suspension
especially in cold weather
felt through the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake and alignment issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, damage to the vehicle, and potential injury to occupants.
symptoms: Vehicle has a hard time going backwards
damages to wheels
frame
and body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair or address issues under warranty can lead to ongoing problems, safety risks, and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealership claims that issues are characteristic of the vehicle and will not attempt to repair under warranty
lack of parts for recall repairs.
